    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-12-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-12-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="561"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d561">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Moscow Embassy Files: Lot F–96</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The American Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dooman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the People’s Commissar for Foreign Affairs of
                        the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Molotov</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. L–23</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-12-23">December 23,
                            1942</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that I have
                    been instructed to transmit the following message from President Roosevelt,
                    dated December 21, 1942, to Premier Stalin.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“I am very sorry arrangements for conference could not be made but I can well
                        understand your position. This will acknowledge your note about the
                        Anglo-American squadrons.<note n="26" xml:id="d561fn26">Note of December 18,
                                <ref target="#pg_677">p. 677</ref>.</note> We will expedite delivery
                        of planes to the utmost. I have arranged to get you ten transport planes in
                        January.</p>
                    <p>“I am writing you in regard to certain post war activities.”</p>
                </quote>
                <p>Accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Eugene H. Dooman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
